## 1. TD3B: Transition-Directed Discrete Diffusion for Allosteric Binder Generation
**arxiv_id:** 2605.09810 | **upvotes:** 0
https://huggingface.co/papers/2605.09810
**Keywords:** discrete diffusion, generative framework, allosteric binder design, directional transition control, target-aware Direction Oracle
**Summary:** A sequence-based generative framework called TD3B is introduced for designing allosteric binders with specified agonist or antagonist behavior by controlling directional transitions in protein states.

## 2. Fitness aligned structural modeling enables scalable virtual screening
  with AuroBind
**arxiv_id:** 2508.02137 | **upvotes:** 24
https://huggingface.co/papers/2508.02137
**Keywords:** structure-based virtual screening, druggable proteome, atomic-level structural model, direct preference optimization, self-distillation
**GitHub:** https://github.com/GENTEL-lab/AuroBind (41 stars)
**Summary:** AuroBind is a scalable virtual screening framework that fine-tunes atomic-level structural models to predict ligand-bound structures and binding fitness, achieving high hit rates in prospective screens across disease-relevant targets.

## 3. A Large-Scale Dataset and Benchmark: Do Protein-Ligand Models Learn Binding Sites or Just Binding Likelihood?
**arxiv_id:** 2605.24045 | **upvotes:** 1
https://huggingface.co/papers/2605.24045
**Keywords:** protein-ligand modeling, binding-site localization, non-covalent interactions, interaction maps, binary binding prediction
**Summary:** InteractBind presents a large-scale protein-ligand dataset and benchmark for evaluating fine-grained binding-site localization and non-covalent interaction identification, revealing limitations in current models' ability to accurately locate binding sites despite strong binary binding predictions.

## 4. AlloGen: Conformation-Selective Binder Generation with Differential State Scoring
**arxiv_id:** 2606.05474 | **upvotes:** 0
https://huggingface.co/papers/2606.05474
**Keywords:** SE(3)-invariant interface graph transformer, two-phase curriculum, conformational selectivity, state-selectivity scorer, backbone generation
**Summary:** AlloGen is a modular framework that separates backbone generation from a state-selectivity scorer to design protein binders with conformational selectivity, demonstrating experimental validation in calmodulin systems.

